LANDECK, Austria (AP) -- Austrian soldiers took advantage of a  break in heavy snowfall today to mount a rescue of avalanche victims from a stricken Alpine town, joining villagers who dug with their bare hands in a frantic effort to reach those buried below.
*Wednesday, Feb. 24, 1999    	 	More Avalanches in Austria   	LANDECK, Austria (AP) -- Another killer avalanche brought new  heartache to Western Austria today, striking just miles from where rescuers were digging for victims of Europe's worst snowslide this winter.
